  <title>Cogl.Framebuffer.prototype.rotate</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function rotate(angle: Number(gfloat), x: Number(gfloat), y: Number(gfloat), z: Number(gfloat)): void {
    // Gjs wrapper for cogl_framebuffer_rotate()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Multiplies the current model-view matrix by one that rotates the
model around the axis-vector specified by <code>x</code>, <code>y</code> and <code>z</code>. The
rotation follows the right-hand thumb rule so for example rotating
by 10 degrees about the axis-vector (0, 0, 1) causes a small
counter-clockwise rotation.</p>
  <p>Since 1.10</p>
